The Zen Computational Linguistics Toolkit (Version 3.1) is a library of
Objective Caml modules and module interfaces of use for computational
linguistics applications - in the aspects of lexicon representation, 
morphology processing, segmentation and tagging.

Its license is described under the file LICENSE. These programs are 
distributed without warranty, use them at your own risk. 

This software runs under Objective Caml, version 3.12 or more recent. 
The Objective Caml system is available from http://caml.inria.fr/ocaml/
In order to install, under a Unix/Linux system or MacOSX, do "make all" 
in the main directory which will compile all modules and produce a few 
executable applications.

The documentation is in directory DOC, under Postscript format as zen.ps, 
under pdf format as zen.pdf, and under a Web page format as zen.html. 

This library has been used for the implementation of the Sanskrit Library,
available at http://sanskrit.inria.fr/

Gérard Huet
30-07-2012

Description of the various components of the Zen library.

ML sources.

Module interfaces: share.mli sharemod.mli minimap.mli aum0.mli aumt.mli

Modules: pidgin.ml gen.ml list2.ml ascii.ml latin.ml list_iso.ml word.ml 
lexer.ml transducer.ml zipper.ml bintree.ml share.ml sharemod.ml unshare.ml 
trie.ml mini.ml dagify.ml deco.ml lexmap.ml minimap.ml tertree.ml lexicon.ml 
minitertree.ml terdagify.ml make_lex.ml timeshare.ml test.ml unglue.ml 
unglue_test.ml react0.ml reactt.ml regular.ml make_dispatch.ml
make_english_lexicon.ml make_french_lexicon.ml example_dispatch.ml 
sanskrit_dispatch.ml example_engine.ml

Aut format examples: example.aut sanskrit.aut

Scripts and info files: Makefile README COPYRIGHT LICENSE .ocamlinit .depend

Documentation: zen.ps zen.pdf zen.html

